.TH clear "" "" Command
.PC "Clear the screen"
\fBclear\fR
.PP
The command
.B clear
reads the
.B termcap
description of your terminal and uses the information therein to
clear your terminal's screen.
The environmental variable
.B TERM
must define your terminal's type.
.SH "See Also"
.Xr "commands," commands
.Xr "TERM," term
.Xr "termcap" termcap
